.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-UNDO 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-undo \- undo the most recent undoable session operation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch undo
[\fB\-\-force\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B undo
restores the repository state to the point before the most recent undoable
session operation. It restores the index, working tree, session files, and
batch refs recorded in that checkpoint. By default it refuses if later changes
make the checkpoint unsafe to apply.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-force
Overwrite changes made after the undo checkpoint.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-redo (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-abort (1)
